\includegraphics*[width=8.6cm]{Fig2}
\caption{(Color online) Dependence of the (a) longitudinal and (b) transverse conductances on $d$ for finite and $\delta$-barriers. (c) Fermi circles in the leads (inner circle) and barrier (outer circle). The arrows denote the wave vectors of states with positive $x$-component of the velocity and the vertical dashed line indicates the first-order resonance condition. (d) Transmission $T(\varepsilon_\mathrm{F},\theta)$ of a finite barrier as a function of $d$ and $\theta$.}\label{fig:Width}
